And are none of them cached? If I go<p><pre><code>    var w = element.clientWidth;
    var h = element.clientHeight;
</code></pre>
Is that 2 reflows or 1?<p><pre><code>    var w1 = element1.clientWidth;
    var h1 = element1.clientHeight;
    var w2 = element2.clientWidth;
    var h2 = element2.clientHeight;
</code></pre>
Is this 4 reflows, 2, or 1?<p>---<p>reading this article (<a href="https://developers.google.com/web/fundamentals/performance/rendering/avoid-large-complex-layouts-and-layout-thrashing?hl=en" rel="nofollow">https://developers.google.com/web/fundamentals/performance/r...</a>) it sounds like it&#x27;s 0 reflows if nothing has changed. In other words it&#x27;s all cached
